metadata.name: The Coranation Of Napeleon
metadata.description:
The King makes a deal with the Satan.
For immortal life and infinite wealth, The King sacrifices his own daughters to the Satan.
Every daughter is sacrificed at the coronation when they turns 18. 
Satan and demons are bathed in the blood of sacrificed souls.

Jacques-Louis David
"The Coranation Of Napeleon" 
(1805-1807)

I draw Renaissance arts.
I draw by reinterpreting the artwork.
I draw with the freehand drawing technique.
